2011-08-22T04:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-22/south-africa-daybook-anc-party-meeting-strike-advtech-psg.html
South Africa ’s ruling  African
National Congress  concludes a four-day meeting of its national
executive committee.  The party announced on Aug. 19 it will take disciplinary
action against  Julius Malema , the head of its youth wing who has
led a campaign to nationalize the country’s mines, for comments
made about neighboring Botswana and for “sowing division” in
the ANC.  To contact the reporter on this story:
